# KISS CLA configuration for Node B (Engine 2)
# Format: <engineId> <device> <baudRate> <mtu> <maxRate> <flowControl> <srcCall> <srcSSID> <dstCall> <dstSSID>
#
# Entry for CLI (own engine ID = 2) and CLO (remote engine ID = 1)
# Both use the same serial device
# UPDATE device path for your system (Linux: /dev/ttyACM0 or /dev/ttyUSB0)
1 /dev/ttyACM0 1200 64 120 0 G4DPZ 2 G4DPZ 1
2 /dev/ttyACM0 1200 64 120 0 G4DPZ 2 G4DPZ 1
